						<summary>

						<p>The inscription seems to pronounce a ban against members of the royal family receiving any <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> lands belonging to the temple of Kālakāladēvar at Tirukkaḍavūr in Ākkūr-nāḍu a division of Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu, and in the case of ryots against receiving more than two <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> probably on tenancy lease.</p>						

						</summary>
